Overview
--------
The HPCSOM platform is a high-performance computing platform that
supports the QorIQ LX2160A Layerscape Architecture Processor and
the S32V234 Automative Processor.

LX2160A SoC Overview
--------------------
For details, please refer arch/arm/cpu/armv8/fsl-layerscape/doc/README.soc

LX2160HPCSOM board Overview
-----------------------------
DDR Memory
	Two ports of 72-bits (8-bits ECC) DDR4.
	Each port supports 4GB memory with SDRAMs soldered.
	Data rate upto 3.2 GT/s.

SERDES ports
	Thress serdes controllers (24 lanes)

	Serdes1:
	  Supports PCIe Gen2 x3, but not used
	  Supports PCIe Gen2 x1 connectivity to S32V234
	  Supports PCIe Gen3 x4 connectivity to baseboard

	Serdes2:
	  Support three SGMII lanes, but not used
	  Supports one SGMII connectivity to baseboard
	  Supports PCIe Gen3 x4 connectivity to baseboard

	Serdes3: Not used

eSDHC
	eSDHC1: Supports a SD connector for connecting SD cards
	eSDHC2: Supports 128GB eMMC memory MICRON MTFC128GAPALNS-AAT

I2C	LTC3882, PMIC1, and PMIC2 accessible on I2C1
	LX2 I2C3 and S32V I2C0 connected

USB 3.0
	One high speed USB 3.0 connectivity to baseboard

Serial Ports	One UART port
Ethernet	One RGMII interface
Debug		ARM JTAG support

Booting Options
---------------
a) eMMC boot
b) SD boot

Memory map for sd/eMMC card
----------------------------
Image							SD/eMMC card Offset
bl2_sd.pbl (RCW+PBI+bl2.pbl)				0x00008
fip.bin (bl31 + bl33(u-boot) +
	 header for Secure-boot(secure-boot only))	0x00800
Boot firmware Environment				0x02800
DDR PHY Firmware (fip_ddr_all.bin)			0x04000
DPAA2 MC Firmware					0x05000
DPAA2 DPL						0x06800
DPAA2 DPC						0x07000
Kernel.itb						0x08000
